==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grocery
<hw>Gro"cer*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Groceries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F. <ets>grosserie</ets>
wholesale. See <er>Grocer</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The commodities
sold by grocers, as tea, coffee, spices, etc.; -- in the United States
almost always in the plural form, in this sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A deal box . . . to carry <qex>groceries</qex> in.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The shops at which the best families of the neighborhood bought
<qex>grocery</qex> and millinery.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A retail grocer's shop or store.</def> <mark>[U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>groenendael</ent>⟦br⟧
